main event: An unidentified aerial object was sighted over Los Alamos, New Mexico, on February 25, 1950.
interesting points: The sighting lasted between 5 seconds to 2 minutes,Observers reported the object coming out of clouds and heading toward the ground,The object varied in distance from 4 to 20 miles from the observers,The shape of the object was circular or resembling a plane fuselage,The object exhibited fluttering or wobbling motion and had a bright and glaring luminosity.
